A SCOTS <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Soldier" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Soldier" target="_blank">soldier</a> who stamped on a man 18 <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Times" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Times" target="_blank">times</a> as he lay defenceless on the ground is facing <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Prison" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Prison" target="_blank">jail</a> and being thrown out of the Army in disgraceShaun <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Smiths" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Smiths" target="_blank">Smith</a> 25 of the Scots Guards was caught on <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Closed-circuit_television" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Closed-circuit_television" target="_blank">CCTV</a> bringing his <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bootleg_recording" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bootleg_recording" target="_blank">boot</a> down again and again on his victim's head and upper bodySmith and his comrade Jason Collins were seen close to their barracks âpummellingâ two men last April a <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Court" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Court" target="_blank">court</a> heard yesterdayOne victim was knocked unconscious and <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Left-wing_politics" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Left-wing_politics" target="_blank">left</a> lying in the road while the other suffered a horrific beatingCCTV footage shows <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Smiths" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Smiths" target="_blank">Smith</a> from Livingston stamping on both men's heads and repeatedly booting one victim while Welsh Guardsman Collins 21 punches him on the groundThe pair ran off and hid in a stream when <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Police" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Police" target="_blank">police</a> turned up at the scene near Catterick Garrison in <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Oliver_North"