 threatened to <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stabbing" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stabbing" target="_blank">stab</a> themBut Paul Abrahams <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Prosecutor" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Prosecutor" target="_blank">prosecuting</a> said their <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Violence" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Violence" target="_blank">violence</a> was a âloss of controlâ and they were never at risk of harmHow the incident started wasn't picked up by the <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Closed-circuit_television" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Closed-circuit_television" target="_blank">security cameras</a> but the horrific <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Violence" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Violence" target="_blank">violence</a> that followed was caught on film and played to the <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jury" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jury" target="_blank">jury</a> during the trialsAfter his <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Arrest" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Arrest" target="_blank">arrest</a> <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Smiths" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Smiths" target="_blank">Smith</a> told <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Police" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Police" target="_blank">police</a> he had been drinking in Darlington County Durham with Collins before returning to the barracks He said he had had gin and cranberry cocktails tequila and more gin on his night outSmith initially claimed he had only kicked his victim but under crossexamination admitted stampingCollins also claimed he thought he was using only necessary force at the <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Time_%28magazine%29" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Time_%28magazine%29" target="_blank">time</a> and denied he had âsnappedâThe <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Soldier" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Soldier" target="_blank"